ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is a study of an array of canonical eighteenth-century philosophy (Burke, Hume, Locke, etc) paired with literature of the eighteenth century and very modern critical works. I would recommend this course to another student--it was beneficial in many ways to my own critical thinking and my writing.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Though I am not studying the period covered by this course, I came away from this class with an impressive list of heavy reading completed, all of which I have used and will continue to use in my own research in the future.
